[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "As the Known things are finite, but there is no limit on the things to know, the only conclusion is our understanding is appoximently  0%."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Just to put a bow how little we understand, because \"Things to Know\" are infinite and Know Things\" are finite it follows \"Unknown Things\" are also infinite! So it does not matter how much we learn we will always know less then we don't know."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Understanding is then easily defined as the percent of \"Things to Know\" that are \"Known Things\"."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Let start by looking at \"Things to know\", this is the sum of all of the \"Known Things\" and all of the \"Unknown Things\".  "
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "H1",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Embracing Uncertainty or \"You Know Nothing Erik Summerfield\""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I was pondering how much I know and don't know and how they should affect how I make decisions. I have been a pusher of uncertainty (just see my blog post "
      },
      {
        "data": {
          "openModal": true,
          "slatenode": {
            "href": "https://www.phase2technology.com/blog/estimate-pirate-use-old"
          }
        },
        "type": "Link",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Estimate like a Pirate use a B.O.A.T"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": ") and thought maybe if I do the math it would be a good way to show people that they should be less certain then they are.  Well, I found that in fact, I was being "
      },
      {
        "text": "too",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " certain, and actually, "
      },
      {
        "text": "I know ",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "nothing",
        "Bold": true,
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "So take a moment and let that sinking in we know so little that we understand 0% of what there is to know.  And no matter how much you learn that is always an "
      },
      {
        "text": "infinite",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " amount more that you don't know."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "..."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Ok glad you let that sink in because it is about to get worse."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Time: Taking Uncertainty to 11!"
      }
    ]
  }
]

{
  "content": "Embracing Uncertainty or \"You Know Nothing Erik Summerfield\""
}

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "How can it get worse you ask? Time, time takes our uncertainty to eleven.  "
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "For anything we knew yesterday, there is some non-zero chance that that is not true today and therefore not known today"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  }
]

{
  "math": "\\forall  d  \\in \\text{Days},  \\forall x \\in \\text{Known Things}_{d-1}, \\\\ p = P(x \\in  X,  x \\not \\in  \\text{Known Things}_d ) \\land p > 0"
}

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Introducing time shows \"Known Things\" is zero and we still have infinite \"Things to Know.\""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "So now we really do not know anything."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "But that percent chance is not known! So then we just can't believe anything even if we knew it yesterday."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
